node.text:
This year's #Sandhurst Tom Surdyke Leadership Award winner goes to Cadet Ethan Erickson with The College of Saint Benedict Saint John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion.

The award is named in memory of Cadet Thomas Surdyke who died from injuries sustained while saving the life of a drowning stranger. Surdyke was a member of the Company B4 @b4_buffaloes Sandhurst team his Plebe year.

After a long grueling process, five teams were named the top teams of the Sandhurst Military Skills Competition.  During Sandhurst, 44 teams representing four U.S. service academies and 16 ROTC programs compete against one another in a variety of military related contests.

Congratulations to USMA Black who won the overall competition. The top teams are: 

1. USMA Black @usma_sandhurst 
2. USMA Gold
3. Company F1 @f1.firehouse 
4. University of North Georgia @ungcadets 
5. The College of St. Benedict St. John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion

node.text:
We honor the legacy of Henry O. Flipper for his perseverance and courage to graduate from the U.S. Military Academy and serve in the #USArmy. Flipper went on to command African-American Soldiers when he assumed command of Troop A, 10th Cavalry Regiment, also known as the Buffalo Soldiers, at Fort Sill, Oklahoma. 

#Blackhistorymonth

node.text:
Since 1992, America honors Buffalo Soldiers on July 28 to commemorate the first Army regiments comprised of African American Soldiers. 

The U.S. Military Academy salutes Buffalo Soldiers who served their country with pride and distinction at West Point. 

In September, the Buffalo Soldier Association of West Point will unveil a new monument at the U.S. Military Academy to be dedicated to the legacy of these elite horsemen. 

#USMA #WestPoint #buffalosoldiers #buffalosoldiermuseum #GoArmy

Command Sgt. Maj. Michael Coffey and Master Sgt. Eric Engstrom presented Soldiers from the 1st Brigade Combat Team, 10th Mountain Division, with powder blue medallions during the Sergeant Audie Murphy Induction Ceremony on July 23 at the U.S. Military Academy.

Induction and membership in the Sergeant Audie Murphy Club is an esteemed honor for Noncommissioned Officers (NCOs) whose leadership achievements and performance merit special recognition. The SAMC is a means of recognizing those NCOs who have contributed significantly to the development of a professional NCO Corps and a combat ready Army. Members exemplify leadership characterized by personal concern for the needs, training, development and welfare of Soldiers and concern for families of soldiers.

#sergeantaudiemurphyclub #goarmy🇺🇸 #westpoint 

📸: Jorge Garcia

Cadets are deep into their Field Training Exercise, moving between lanes, setting up their patrol base, and working on attack and defense operations. Four platoons fight in the same battlespace in a "sandbox" style match where forces can maneuver at their discretion. The defending platoons occupy a small village and are tasked with defending a bridge. They have a few hours to fortify positions and emplace obstacles while the attacking forces close in and recon their positions. The attacking platoons are given minimal restrictive guidance and are free to execute their attack however they see fit. #GoArmy #WestPoint #CLDT #USMA2022 #USMA2023 @usma.dmi 

📸: Cadet Marco Copat

The 124th New York Infantry Regiment Civil War re-enactors teach cadets how to properly wield black powder muskets during the Overland Campaign Staff Ride, which is a hands-on Civil War Drill, Tuesday on The Plain. The cadets are conducting a week-long intensive study of Civil War campaigns, including the Overland Campaign, Petersburg Campaign and the Appomattox Campaign, which ended the Civil War.    

📸: Jorge Garcia/Pointer View

node.text:
Cadet Leader Development Training (CLDT) tests warrior skills. During a situational training exercise, platoons conduct Air Assault operations and road march to their area of operations. Cadets spend the night in the field conducting patrol base operations and lanes before marching back. During Warrior Week and Cold Load training, trainees review their basic warrior tasks and drills within platoons to prepare for the upcoming 10-day field training exercise, which includes battle drills, weapon disassembly and cleaning, planning, briefs, and patrol base operations. During Cold Load Training, cadets do dry runs by boarding and unloading from Black Hawk and Chinook helicopters in preparation for upcoming Air Assault operations.  For more CLDT photos, visit West Point Flickr. #USMA #WestPoint #USMA2022 #USMA2023 #Leadership #GoArmy

📸: Cadet Marco Copat, Class of 2022

The Class of 2025 enjoyed a relaxing afternoon with West Point families, faculty, and staff on Cadet Visitation Day which officially completes Cadet Basic Training I. New cadets reconnected with family and friends on cell phones and spent time learning more about their host, West Point, and the Army family. Stay tuned for more photos as the new cadets kick-start Cadet Basic Training II with their new cadre. Thanks to all the families who welcomed the new cadets into their homes. #WestPoint #USMACBT #USMA2025

📸: Jorge Garcia/Pointer View
